How to contribute to the Chrome Games:

1. Feature requests and bug fixes
- Use GitHub issues for filing bugs and suggesting feature additions.

If there is already an issue that you would like to resolve, post on it volunteering to do the coding.
If there is not a relevant issue, create one. 

2. Discussion with team
- All discussion can happen within the GitHub issues thread

3. Style guide
- We follow Google's JavaScript style guides, found at: https://google.github.io/styleguide/jsguide.html

4. Pull requests
- Make sure to create a separate branch if you are working on a new feature

5. Code reviews
- The lead developer, @tsammons, will provide personal code reviews for each pull request
